<div class="wrap"><h2><?php print WP2M_PUGIN_NAME . " settings" ?></h2><p>This plugin allows you to place a shortcode in a post that passes encrypted logon information to Moodle, using the <a href="#github link">Wp2Moodle authentication plugin</a> for Moodle 2.2. The user will be created (if required) by Moodle and enrolled in the specified Cohort.</p><p>Example link: <em>[wp2moodle class='css-classname' cohort='class1' target='_blank']my link text[/wp2moodle]</em>, or use the button on the editor toolbar.</p><form method="post" action="options.php">    <?php		settings_fields( 'wp2m-settings-group' );	?>    <table class="form-table">    	<tr valign="top">    		<th scope="row">Plugin version:</th>    		<td><?php print WP2M_CURRENT_VERSION ?></td>    	</tr>        <tr valign="top">	        <th scope="row">Moodle URL</th>	        <td><input type="text" name="wp2m_moodle_url" value="<?php echo get_option('wp2m_moodle_url'); ?>" size="60" />	        <span class="description">Plugin will append the url <em><?php echo L2M_MOODLE_PLUGIN_URL ?></em>.</span>	        </td>        </tr>                 <tr valign="top">    	    <th scope="row">Encryption secret</th>        	<td><input type="text" name="wp2m_shared_secret" value="<?php echo get_option('wp2m_shared_secret'); ?>" size="60" />        	<span class="description">Must match setting on Moodle plugin</span>        	</td>        </tr>            </table>        <p class="submit">    <input type="submit" class="button-primary" value="<?php _e('Save Changes') ?>" />    </p></form></div>